    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>Tyler is the most slavish person one could ever know, he's a show off and always tries to be cool. He wants to bring forth chaos on the web which he calls \"Project Mayhem\".</p>\n<p>In this project of his, he tried to hack into the college server to manipulate personal information of other students. Tyler, notices that he has <b>N</b> tasks to do after getting into the server, and every <b>i<sup>th</sup></b> task takes <b>K<sub>i</sub></b> seconds.</p>\n<p>Being a Script Kiddie, he has some predefined scripts that can perform certain tasks but for some tasks he will have to use his own brain. You can't let the predefined script perform three tasks listed consecutively as the system would detect intrusion in that case.</p>\n<p>Now, Tyler doesn't really like to use his brain much, and would like to minimize the amount of time spent with non automated tasks.</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases.</li>\n<li>The first line of each test case contains a single integer <b>N</b> denoting the total number of tasks. The second line contains <b>N</b> space-separated integers <b>K<sub>1</sub></b>, <b>K<sub>2</sub></b>, ..., <b>K<sub>N</sub></b> denoting the required time for <b>i<sup>th</sup></b> task.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case output a single integer denoting the minimum time for which Tyler needs to use his brain.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>20</b></li>\n<li><b>10</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>K<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>3</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n7\n4 2 7 1 3 2 8\n9\n2 1 3 4 6 3 1 8 9\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n5\n6\n\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> 2 + 1 + 2 = 5</p>\n<p><b>Example case 2.</b> 1 + 4 + 1 = 6</p>",
